cal authority is responsible for the education at Future Academies?  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">When there is a breakdown in funding, a lack of resources for the schools, when parents need help advocating for their</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> school</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> budgets or for their children</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">’s education,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> who are they to turn to for help?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Does the council have any responsibility for children’s education when they are in an academy or free school?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">When children with special needs are not receiving specialist instruction or devices to help them learn, who is in the council is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">responsible to help ensure that their needs are met?</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Pimlico Primary</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">As a result of the opening of an additional reception class at Pimlico Primary, there are not enough children to fill the reception class at St. Gabriel’s School. What other schools in south Westminster are unable to fill their reception classes?  St. Barnabas? Churchill Gardens?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">How is the council going to address the drain on budgets at the council schools by the free schools?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What is the curriculum that is being used at Pimlico Primary?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Will Pimlico Primary have a head or will they share a head with Millbank and Churchill Gardens?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">How will Future ensure that parents are able to meet with teachers and managers?  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Who will be overseeing the instruction and watching the curriculum?  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">When I was a teacher in Kensington and Chelsea, my head observed my teaching, checked my lesson plans, checked my students’ exercise books to make sure I was teaching and more importantly that they were learning.  How will this take place in the academy system, will the Deputy Heads and Key Stage managers take on this responsibility? </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Churchill Gardens School:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Curriculum:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Churchill Gardens has a very unique population of children, most of whom come from happy, loving homes where English is not the mother tongue.  In the past, Westminster has had strong educational outcomes with this kind of population because they have put in place the best practice in curriculum – these practices include play-based, language-rich, hands-on, concrete lessons.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What provisions will the curriculum used by Future Academies have for children for whom English is an additional language?  How will Future maintain the strong outcomes for children who do not speak English?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">How is Future planning to communicate with the non-English speaking families who support the children at Churchill Gardens?  Will the non-English speaking families be able to participate?</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Speech and Language Unit:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Is there a ring-fence around the Speech and Language unit? This is an essential service for families in any council, but this is an expensive and specialist service.  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What provisions has Future in place to ensure that this essential council service is maintained at its current standard?</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Playground:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What is the reasoning behind removing a playground from a school?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Is the play scheme at Sussex Street going to be moved to Churchill Gardens?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What will happen to the land at Sussex Street?  Who hold the lease? What are the plans for development?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What is the “old caretakers house” what is it currently being used as?  Is that where the early years are held?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What is Darwin House used as currently?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Who is ensuring the transparency of the development of the land in Churchill Gardens?  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Who is awarding the contracts and who is ensuring that there is no conflict of interest?</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&